<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="W-gen-policies" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>General Course Policies</title>

<section xml:id="course-culture">
    <title>Virtual Classroom Culture</title>
    <p>We will focus on fostering a growth mindset where students are encouraged to persevere through confusion, learn from mistakes, and take ownership of their learning. I encourage all students to ask for help when they need it and give help when they are able via the <em>Ask a Peer | Help a Peer</em> discussion board in Canvas.
</p>
<p>I ask that all students work with me to create a welcoming environment that is respectful of all forms of diversity, including but not limited to diversity in parenting status, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, race, religion, and socioeconomic status. Just as you are expected to call me Mrs. Green and use the pronouns she/her for me, each student will be given the opportunity to identify their preferred name and pronouns, and other <em>students are expected to be respectful and use the correct name and pronouns when referring to fellow students</em>.
</p>
</section>

<section xml:id="course-format">
    <title>Course Format</title>
    <p>This course utilizes web-based instruction. While the majority of your learning, assignments, and interaction will occur online, this course includes a mandatory in-person midterm and final exam.</p>
        <subsection xml:id="required-meetings">
            <title>Required Meetings</title>
             <p>There are no required weekly meetings; however, the midterm and final exams must be attended in person.</p>
        </subsection>
        <subsection xml:id="support-collaboration">
            <title>Support &amp; Collaboration</title>
            
            <p>You are encouraged to attend in-person or virtual office hours, schedule virtual appointments as needed, and organize your own study groups for help with the course content.</p>
        </subsection>
</section>

<section xml:id="attendance-participation">
    <title>Attendance and Participation</title>
    <p>Other than academic participation, there is no official “attendance” grade for the course. I will, however, track participation on assignments and monitor activity in Canvas throughout the semester to make sure no one is falling too far behind. If you do get behind, please do let me know so that we can work out your next steps.
</p>
<warning><p>Students <alert>MUST</alert> complete an academic assignment by the official census date (see the <url href="https://www.midland.edu/academics/academic-calendars.php">MC Academic Calendar</url> for this date). Students who do not complete an academic assignment before the end of Census Day will be reported as "never attended" and dropped from the course, per Midland College policy.</p>
</warning>
</section>